{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:56:39.827435+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e460887e6e08f3b03d5bc7a0c902fbc6dcf176c2)", "id": "lc_e3c7664e-9b44-43db-8335-a0a20e92e043"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Command-line entry point for gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\n\nfrom . import git_ops\nfrom .config import load_config\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"gwc\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"gwc 0.1.0\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"status-summary\",\n        help=\"Print a one-line summary of the current branch state.\",\n    )\n\n    p_branch = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"branch-name\",\n        help=\"Generate a conventional branch name for an issue.\",\n    )\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"issue_number\", type=int)\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"slug\", type=str)\n\n    p_clean = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"clean-merged\",\n        help=\"List or delete local branches fully merged into main.\",\n    )\n    p_clean.add_argument(\n        \"--apply\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        default=False,\n        help=\"Actually delete branches (default is dry-run).\",\n    )\n\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n    config = load_config()\n\n    if args.command == \"status-summary\":\n        print(git_ops.status_summary())\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"branch-name\":\n        prefix = config.get(\"branch_name\", {}).get(\"prefix\", \"issue-\")\n        print(f\"{prefix}{args.issue_number}-{args.slug}\")\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"clean-merged\":\n        protected = config.get(\"clean_merged\", {}).get(\n            \"protected_branches\", [\"main\", \"develop\"]\n        )\n        merged = git_ops.list_merged_branches(protected=protected)\n        if not merged:\n            print(\"No merged branches to delete.\")\n            return 0\n        if args.apply:\n            for b in merged:\n                git_ops.delete_branch(b)\n            print(f\"Deleted: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Would delete: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        return 0\n\n    parser.error(f\"unknown command: {args.command}\")\n    return 2\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_979c842e-dd9a-4fba-afe3-628f95111beb"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "11938d44-fe99-4ca8-9c9c-b96e0f734619", "tool_call_id": "call_d4bdc26175ba468fb8313a7e", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:56:44.170617+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a complete picture. Here's the onboarding summary:\n\n---\n\n## Command-line tool: `gwc`\n\nThe package installs a CLI command called **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion), defined in `pyproject.toml` as:\n\n```\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n```\n\n### What `gwc` currently does\n\nIt's a subcommand-based CLI with three commands:\n\n1. **`gwc status-summary`** — Prints a one-line summary of the current branch state (delegates to `git_ops.status_summary()`).\n\n2. **`gwc branch-name <issue_number> <slug>`** — Generates a conventional branch name for an issue. It combines a configurable prefix (default `\"issue-\"`) with the issue number and slug to produce something like `issue-42-fix-login-bug`. Prefix can be overridden via config.\n\n3. **`gwc clean-merged [--apply]`** — Lists local branches that are fully merged into `main` (the \"protected branches\" list defaults to `[\"main\", \"develop\"]` but is configurable). Without `--apply` it runs in **dry-run** mode (just prints what *would* be deleted). With `--apply` it actually deletes those branches.\n\nIt also supports `--version` (prints `gwc 0.1.0`) and loads configuration from a config file via `config.load_config()`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 328, "prompt_tokens": 5468, "total_tokens": 5796, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 24, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4864, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0001900192, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 9.81792e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 9.184e-05}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-2